Bloodstone Manhunter							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General														PRETEXT:Bloodstone Swords 10 TPA.																DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You are skilled at fighting criminal humans such as bandits.																																SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:You gain a +1 bonus on Bluff, Knowledge, Perception, Sense Motive, and Survival checks against humans, and a +1 bonus on weapon attack and damage rolls against humans. If you have a favored enemy bonus against humans, this feat does not stack with that bonus.																														ASPECT:SkillBonus|You gain a +1 bonus on Bluff, Knowledge, Perception, Sense Motive, and Survival checks against humans.|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy ~ Humanoid (Human)	ASPECT:CombatBonus|You gain a +1 bonus on Attack rolls and Damage rolls against humans.|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy ~ Humanoid (Human)
Calm Disposition								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General														PRETEXT:Prophets of Kalistrade 10 TPA.															DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You always appear to be in control of your situation.																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:You gain +2 bonus on saving throws against effects that affect your composure. This includes all mind-affecting spells, as well as any spell or ability that would cause you to behave in an out-of-control manner, such as fear effects and nausea. This does not include physical effects such as fatigue, and does not reduce any damage taken from concurrent effects.													ASPECT:SaveBonus|You gain +2 bonus on saving throws against effects that affect your composure.
Death's Suitor								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General														PRETEXT:Risen Guard 20 TPA.																	DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You have died and returned so often that even Pharasma now deems it part of your fate.																											SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:Once per day, you may reroll a save or skill check if failure has a chance of killing you (whether from hit point damage, ability damage, or some instant effect). You must decide to use this ability before the results are revealed. You must take the second roll, even if it is worse.
Disassemble Magic Item							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General	PREABILITY:1,Category=Feat,TYPE.ItemCreation						PRETEXT:Any item creation feat, Aspis Consortium 20 TPA.												DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You can take apart and reassemble magic items.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:You can break a magic item down into component pieces. Disassembling a magic item takes 1 hour per 1,000 gp of the item's price. You can only use this feat on items your item creation feat would let you craft. You may reassemble a dismantled item as long as all the pieces are present; this takes the same amount of time as taking it apart did. There is a 10%% chance the reconstruction fails and the item is permanently destroyed.
Divine Deception								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General	PRESKILL:2,Knowledge (religion)=5,Use Magic Device=5					PRETEXT:Knowledge (religion) 5 ranks, Use Magic Device 5 ranks.														DESC:You are skilled at manipulating divine magical items.																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:You gain a +5 bonus on Use Magic Device checks to use divine spell-trigger or spell completion items or to emulate a divine class feature.
Fast Crawl									CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																						DESC:You are skilled at moving while prone.																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:While prone, you can move at half speed. This movement provokes attacks of opportunity as normal. You can take a 5-foot step while crawling. This benefit does not stack with the rogue crawl talent.
Fearsome Barricade							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat		PRESKILL:1,Intimidate=5										PRETEXT:Intimidate 5 ranks, Ulfen Guard TPA 20.														DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Your wrath is as potent a barrier as your blades.																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:Choose an adjacent ally as a free action on your turn. Once per round, when an opponent attacks that ally, you may make an Intimidate check to demoralize the opponent as an immediate action. This action counts as an attack of opportunity.
Grand Master Performer							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General	PRECLASS:1,Bard=8		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Master Performer		PRETEXT:Bardic performance class feature, Extra Performance, Master Performer, bard level 8th, Kitharodian Academy 20 TPA.	DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You grant your allies even greater bonuses when using your bardic performance abilities.																											SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:When any of your bardic performance abilities grant your allies a bonus, that bonus increases by +1. This bonus stacks with the bonus from the Master Performer feat.
